 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO Three ex-convicts, Adebayo Gbenga, 33; Agun Busayo Tope, 33; and Ogunmusuru Seun, 30, have been remanded in Ilesa Correctional Centre by a Magistrate’s Court over an allegation of robbery. The police accused the trio of breaking into about seven homes in Osogbo, the Osun State capital at night, with guns and other dangerous weapons. According to police prosecutor, Inspector Temitope Fatoba, the defendants robbed the residents of their phones, money, wristwatch, schoolbag, jewelry, clothes and shoes among other items, about five weeks after serving initial jail terms at the Ilesa Correctional Centre for robbery. Fatoba said that the accused persons dispossessed their victims of their Automated Teller Machine cards and withdrew some amount of money from their bank accounts. The charge brought against them read that “Adebayo Gbenga, Agun Busayo Tope, and Ogunmusuru Seun, and others now at large, between September 17 and December 30, 2021, at night time in Osogbo, Osun State, did conspire among yourselves to commit a felony to wit: armed robbery. “You did arm yourselves with guns and other dangerous weapons and robbed one Aboderin Samuel of one iPhone, one Samsung phone, one Nokia phone, one Apple wristwatch valued at N120,000, a wedding band valued at N200,000, two Patiek watches valued at N100,000, (and) cash sum of N84,200; all items stolen valued at N844,000. “You armed yourselves with guns and other dangerous weapons and robbed one Alao Oluwaronke of gold jewelries valued at N600, 000, two computers valued at N300, 000, clothes and shoes worth N300, 000, car key and the sum of N29, 000 transferred from bank account. “You (defendants) did arm yourselves with guns, and other dangerous weapons and rob one Ajayi Bilikis of one iPhone 7 valued at N80,000, one iPhone 6S valued at N60,000, Infinix Hot 5 valued at N37,500, one itel phone valued at N5,000, a 16gig memory card valued at N3,000 and one bag. “You robbed one Abolarin Omolola of two Tecno phones valued at N74, 500, three small phones valued at N15, 000, a neck chain valued at N4, 000, memory card valued at N4, 000 and cash sum of N4, 000. “You did arm yourselves with guns and other dangerous weapons and rob one Olije Folasade of seven mobile phones valued at N321,900, PS4 game valued at N150,000, jewelry valued at N10,000, Rolex gold watch valued at N25,000, clothes, perfumes and shoes, all valued at N748,400.” He added that the trio robbed one Adejumo Busayo of two Infinix mobile phones valued at N120, 000, Amazon tablet valued at N150, 000, schoolbag valued at N30, 000, power bank valued at N15,000, and the sum of N320,000. He alleged that they also dispossessed one Alabi Mariam of one iPhone 12 valued at N700,000, gold earrings valued at N75,000, wristwatch valued at N45,000, shoes and clothes valued at N35,000, and a Zenith Bank ATM card which they allegedly used to transfer the sum of N150,000 from her (Mariam’s) bank account. The prosecutor said that the defendants committed offences contrary to sections 6(b), punishable under sections 1(1) and 1(1)(2)(a)(b) of the Robbery and Firearms (Special Provisions) Act Cap RII, Volume 14 Laws of Federation of Nigeria, 2004. Their plea was turned down because of the severity of the charge. Magistrate M. A. Olatunji ordered that the three defendants should be remanded in Ile-Ife Correctional Centre pending legal advice by the Department of Public Prosecution, Osun State Ministry of Justice. The case was adjourned till July 18 for mention. 